## Steps to reproduce the issue
    module TOP(a, b, y);
      input [3:0] a, b;
      output [2:0] y;
      reg [2:0] tmp;
      wire NC;
      sub p(a, b, {NC, tmp});
      assign y = tmp;
    endmodule
    
    module sub(as, bs, ys);
      input [3:0] as, bs;
      output [3:0] ys;
      assign ys = as & bs;
    endmodule

```
read_verilog test.v
prep
splitnets
rmports
delete w:NC
clean -purge
rmports
splitnets -ports
rmports
clean -purge
opt_clean -purge

```
## Expected behavior
module sub should have 3bit wide output ys instead of 4.

## Actual behavior
module sub ys[3] is not used by design and according to "help rmports"

> This pass identifies ports in the selected modules which are not used or
> driven and removes them.
>
